HEADWORD: Distoma
<hw>Dis"to*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <grk>sto`ma</grk>
mouth.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of parasitic, trematode
worms, having two suckers for attaching themselves to the part they
infest. See 1st <er>Fluke</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
